        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Istanbul mayor arrested</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/ekrem-imamoglu-istanbul-mayor-detention.png" alt="Istanbul Mayor Ekrem ƒ∞mamoƒülu speaking at a public event, holding a microphone and gesturing with his hand. Detention by Turkish authorities over alleged corruption and terror links." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Istanbul‚Äôs Mayor Ekrem Imamoglu. Credits: Emrah Gurel/Associated Press</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Turkish authorities detained Istanbul Mayor Ekrem Imamoglu, President Erdogan‚Äôs main political rival. He was taken in the morning during a raid over alleged <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-03-2025-h2-2-corruption-and-terror-links" target="_blank">corruption and terror links</a>. Prosecutors also issued warrants for around 100 people, including businessmen and journalists. Imamoglu‚Äôs detention comes days before his expected nomination as the opposition presidential candidate. 
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The authorities revoked his university diploma, disqualifying him from running for president. Turkish law requires candidates to hold a degree. Imamoglu faces two investigations, one for bribery and tender rigging and the other for allegedly aiding the Kurdistan Workers Party. The move sparked protests, with crowds gathering outside police headquarters demanding his release. </p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Authorities banned demonstrations in Istanbul and restricted access to social media. Human rights groups, Germany, and the Council of Europe condemned the detention. Imamoglu vowed not to give up, saying, ‚ÄúThe will of the people cannot be silenced through intimidation.‚Äù Opposition leaders called the arrest an attempted coup against their future presidential candidate.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
