            <strong>üáßüáæ Belarus sentences a Japanese man to 7 years for espionage</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          A court in Belarus has sentenced Japanese citizen Masatoshi Nakanishi to seven years in prison for espionage. He was accused of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-20-03-2025-br1-4-photographing-military-and-civilian-sites" target="_blank">photographing military and civilian sites</a> and sharing the images with Japanese intelligence. They allege this took place along the Belarus-Ukraine border from 2018 to 2024. Nakanishi, who was living in Gomel and teaching Japanese at a local university, was arrested in July 2024.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">His trial was held behind closed doors, and Belarusian authorities rejected Japan‚Äôs request to attend. He was also fined roughly $6,600. Japan demanded his immediate release, while Belarusian state media aired a program accusing him of spying. Human rights groups declared him a political prisoner. This case is one of the crackdowns on foreign nationals in Belarus.</p>
        </mj-text>
